<plot>Emma B. Freeman was a world famous feminist photographer working in 1915 rural northern California. She made her studio a salon for outcasts, and crossed the line between "white" and Indian" cultures to create her romantic hand painted photographs of the Yurok tribe. Derided as a Bohemian by small-town Victorian society, her sexual openness lead to a major scandal and her tragic death at a young age.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?344536</url></doc>
